 Scotland":"Perth, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Dumbarton, Dunbartonshire, Scotland":"Dumbarton, Dunbartonshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Dunbar","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from Dunbar, a place on the North Sea coast near Edinburgh, named with Gaelic <i>dùn</i> ‘fort’ + <i>barr</i> ‘top, summit’.","History: A family of this name were granted the lands of Dunbar by Malcolm III (1058–1093), and later acquired the earldoms of Dunbar and March. These earldoms were then withdrawn from the family by James I in 1434."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Dunbar was born in 1390, in Dumbarton, Dunbartonshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Sir Malcolm Colquhoun Baron of Luss. She died in 1438, in her hometown, at the age of 48."},"et":{"1390–1438":"1390–1438","1387–1439":"1387–1439","1410–1454":"1410–1454","1420–1479":"1420–1479","1479":"1479","1410":"1410","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1387":"1387","1390":"1390","1439":"1439","1438":"1438","Luss, Dunbartonshire, Scotland":"Luss, Dunbartonshire, Scotland","Perth, Perthshire, Scotland":"Perth, Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Dumbarton, Dunbartonshire, Scotland":"Dumbarton, Dunbartonshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1390–1438":"1390–1438","1387–1439":"1387–1439","1410–1454":"1410–1454","1420–1479":"1420–1479","1479":"1479","1410":"1410","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1387":"1387","1390":"1390","1439":"1439","1438":"1438","Luss, Dunbartonshire, Scotland":"Luss, Dunbartonshire, Scotland","Perth, Perthshire, Scotland":"Perth, Perthshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dumbarton, Dunbartonshire, Scotland":"Dumbarton, Dunbartonshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1390–1438":"1390–1438","1387–1439":"1387–1439","1410–1454":"1410–1454","1420–1479":"1420–1479","1479":"1479","1410":"1410","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1387":"1387","1390":"1390","1439":"1439","1438":"1438","Luss, Dunbartonshire, Scotland":"Luss, Dunbartonshire, Écosse","Perth, Perthshire, Scotland":"Perth, Perthshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Dumbarton, Dunbartonshire, Scotland":"Dumbarton, Dunbartonshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Dunbar est née en 1390, à Dumbarton, Dunbartonshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille avec Sir Malcolm Colquhoun Baron of Luss. Elle est décédée en 1438, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 48 ans."},"de":{"1390–1438":"1390–1438","1387–1439":"1387–1439","1410–1454":"1410–1454","1420–1479":"1420–1479","1479":"1479","1410":"1410","1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1387":"1387","1390":"1390","1439":"1439","1438":"1438","Luss, Dunbartonshire, Scotland":"Luss, Dunbar